---
By: Zhuangzi
Source:
  ID: 50ae0a98-5702-40cb-8c11-4c6297aa457a
  Locus:
    Chapter: 4
    Paragraph: 31
  Title: The Complete Works of Chuang Tzu
  Translator: Burton Watson
Title: In The World Of Men
---
\"Therefore the aphorism says, 'Do not deviate from your orders; do not
press for completion.' To go beyond the limit is excess; to deviate
from orders or press for completion is a dangerous thing. A good
completion takes a long time; a bad completion cannot be changed later.
Can you afford to be careless?
